{
  "stem": "166.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And then as I got bar mitzvah, we went to cheder, and I went to, to school with the [NON-ENGLISH] together, and the other friends.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Later, when the war broke out, everybody starts evacuating.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I remember the 1st of September, they marched into Bedzin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "My father started to-- three days ago he walked away, he evacuated, because there was such a panic that they said that they're going to shoot the men.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So they went further east.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And when the Germans came in, right away, the next day, there were signs on the street-- anybody who has rifles or ammunition should bring it [INAUDIBLE] to the city hall.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And the second day, there was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] signs, you know, all over on the doors-- anybody who has a radio should bring it in.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Or a knife, or anything-- we should bring it into the city hall.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And every, every day there was another order.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Later my father came back already, because the Germans got in fairly close.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "The, the war was already over with Poland, so my father came back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it-- the law started to be so that you cannot go on this side of the street.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "The Jews can only go on one side of the street.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And then we had to move out from this part of the city to another part of the city.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And then we had to wear armbands on the hands with a Jewish star.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And then we had to-- every Jew had to work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "If you didn't work, they had special troops that they came into the town and they start grabbing people on the street.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "So everybody was hiding.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
